SABIE – An unknown number of suspects attempted to rob Standard Bank in Sabie this morning. J&M Security operations manager, Shaun Terblanche, said their patrol vehicle came upon the suspects at around 01:36. ALSO READ: Husband hopes Johanica’s killer found redemption “There was a shootout between my officers and the suspects. Luckily, nobody was injured during the incident.” The suspects fled in two white Mercedes Benzes and a gold Volvo S60 in the direction of Hazyview. Police spokesman Sgt Gerald Sedibe said police are currently looking for the suspects. Anyone with information regarding this can contact Const Mpoloshe Molobela on 071-685-1211.